const faqSchema={"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": [{"@type": "Question", "name": "Is 24 months realistic for first-time home buyers?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "For many first-time buyers, 24 months is realistic and achievable. This timeline allows you to improve credit, save down payment systematically, and educate yourself about the process. Buyers with stronger starting points (higher credit, some savings) might complete in 12-18 months. Those starting with challenges might need 30-36 months. The key is having a realistic plan rather than unrealistic expectations. Use the FHA loan calculator to determine your down payment target and calculate monthly savings needed."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What if I can't save enough in 24 months?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "If saving the full down payment in 24 months seems impossible, explore down payment assistance programs, consider lower-priced properties, or extend your timeline. Many buyers combine personal savings with family gift funds and assistance programs to reach their goal faster. Others use house hacking strategies to buy with minimal down payment and eliminate housing costs immediately. The timeline is a tool, not a rigid requirement\u2014adjust it to your reality while maintaining forward momentum."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "Should I keep renting or buy sooner with less saved?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "This depends on your market and situation. In rapidly appreciating markets, buying sooner with minimal down payment might build more wealth than waiting to save larger amount. In stable markets, having more down payment reduces monthly costs and mortgage insurance. Consider using rent vs buy calculator to model both scenarios. Generally, if you meet minimum requirements and can afford payments comfortably, buying sooner starts building equity sooner."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "How do I stay motivated for 24 months?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Break the timeline into quarterly milestones with specific, achievable targets. Celebrate each milestone reached. Track progress visually where you see it daily. Share your goal with accountability partner who checks in regularly. Remember that every month of rent is money you'll never see again, while every month of homeownership builds equity. Many buyers find motivation increases as they see savings grow and goal becomes more tangible. Consider joining online communities of first-time buyers for mutual support."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What if my circumstances change during these 24 months?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Life changes are normal and expected\u2014plans should flex with reality. Job changes might accelerate or delay timeline. Relationship changes could combine resources or require individual reassessment. Market changes might require price target adjustments. The 24-month roadmap provides structure, not rigid rules. Work with your lender to adapt the plan when circumstances shift, maintaining core objective while adjusting tactics and timeline as needed."}}, {"@type": "Question", "name": "What's Next in Your Journey?", "acceptedAnswer": {"@type": "Answer", "text": "Continue building your Smart Stewards roadmap:"}}]};
const breadcrumbSchema={"@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList", "itemListElement": [{"@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://stairwaymortgage.com/"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Blog", "item": "https://stairwaymortgage.com/blog/"}, {"@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Home Purchase Budget: Your 2-Year Roadmap to Homeownership"}]};
